data.chText: 过剩；剩余；过剩量；剩余额
data.enText: an amount that is extra or more than you need
Wheat was in surplus that year.
the amount by which the amount of money received is greater than the amount of money spent
The balance of payments was in surplus last year (= the value of exports was greater than the value of imports) .
more than is needed or used

data.chText: 过剩的谷物正销往国外。
data.enText: Surplus grain is being sold for export.
These items are surplus to requirements (= not needed) .

simple_means.memory_skill: sur 上；超；外加 + plus 加 → 多余的

ex.chText: 她退休余下的时间都在养花中度过。
ex.enText: She spent the remainder of her retirement growing flowers.
When will the remainder be paid off?
Twenty-eight divided by nine gives you a remainder of 1.

synonyms.bx: 泛指从整体取走或用掉部分后的剩余部分，通常与定冠词 the 连用；也指除法运算中的余数。

ex.chText: 她把晚饭的剩菜扔掉了。
ex.enText: She threw away the remains of her supper.

ex.chText: 几处古罗马遗迹得到了很好的保护。
ex.enText: Several Roman remains have been well protected.

synonyms.bx: 指某物得以保留且未被破坏的部分。

ex.chText: 我们两人每人只能拿两个包，剩下的怎么办？
ex.enText: Each of us can only carry two bags. What about the rest?

ex.chText: 3名银行劫匪被捕，其余的逃走了。
ex.enText: Three of the bank robbers were arrested, and the rest escaped.

ex.chText: 你可以把剩下的西瓜带回宿舍。
ex.enText: You can bring the rest of this watermelon to your dormitory.

ex.chText: 他希望他能在一个安静的村庄里度过余生。
ex.enText: He wished that he could spend the rest of his life in a quiet village.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，通常与定冠词 the 连用。

d: 剩余部分；余下的人（或物）

ex.chText: 是什么造成了原油过剩？
ex.enText: What causes the surplus of crude oil?

ex.chText: 被剪掉的多余部分可以做什么用？
ex.enText: What can we do with the surplus trimmed away?

synonyms.bx: 指超出需求的过剩数量。

tr: a quantity much larger than is needed
more than is needed, desired, or required
example: found some extra change lying on the dresser
yet another book on heraldry might be thought redundant
skills made redundant by technological advance
it was supererogatory of her to gloat
extra ribs as well as other supernumerary internal parts
surplus cheese distributed to the needy

value.def: If there is a surplus of something, there is more than is needed.

example.ex: Germany suffers from a surplus of teachers.
example.tran: 德国遭遇了教师过剩的问题。

value.tran: 过剩;剩余;过剩量;剩余额

value.def: Surplus is used to describe something that is extra or that is more than is needed.

example.ex: Few people have large sums of surplus cash...
I sell my surplus birds to a local pet shop...
example.tran: 我把多余的鸟卖给当地的宠物商店。

example.ex: The houses are being sold because they are surplus to requirements.
example.tran: 这些因超出需求而闲置着的房子正在出售。

gramarinfo.label: usu ADJ n, also v-link ADJ <l>to</l> n

value.def: If a country has a trade surplus, it exports more than it imports.

example.ex: Japan's annual trade surplus is in the region of 100 billion dollars.
example.tran: 日本每年的贸易顺差额在 1,000 亿美元左右。

value.def: If a government has a budget surplus, it has spent less than it received in taxes.

example.ex: Norway's budget surplus has fallen from 5.9% in 1986 to an expected 0.1% this year.
example.tran: 挪威的预算盈余已经从 1986 年的 5.9%降至今年预计的 0.1%。

trans: (可公开出售的)剩余军用物资

sur 上；超；外加 + plus 加 → 多余的
sur 上；超；外加 + real 真实的 → 超现实的
sur 上；超；外加 + realism 现实主义 → 超现实主义
